8.9.19  11:35 am   I saw a transcription for Hello Sexy Pants, and over the "I wanna know why it hurts soooo bad", the chords were: Dmin7D#5 (I) Db6/9 (know) Bbsus/C (hurts) F-9 (so) Eb13sus (bad), is this correct? Maybe I'm doing the wrong voicings, cos it doesn't sound quite right. Thanks!

      i'm not going to listen to it (superstition), but for "i" you probably just want Dmin7b5 (maybe even without the Ab note? don't remember. try both, see which is better). "know" you won't need the Eb note, actually i'd just say that's a Db chord and the vocal is singing the Bb note. "hurts" the way you have it would include F note, don't want that, that's probably just C-7. then "so" take out the G note, and "bad" take out the C note and add F. that should get you there

8.9.19  7:09 am   Hi, Bill. i read that you said: "my secret is just live under a rock" regarding your style of content. in some media it's really hard to come up with anything original if you haven't at least got an overview of the surroundings, just so you don't unknowingly repeat someone else's idea. on the other hand, you've been creating for so long now, your stuff's been maturing in a unique barrel, so it's got to be original in some way or other. do you think being idiosyncratic and persistent enough is a good way to create original content?

     yes

     
also, is it really less reliable than "knowing the literature"? people will say "lone wolf runaway hits are very rare" but still, how likely are you to create something interesting by deducing your way to an idea after analyzing what everyone else has done? maybe there's a balance to strike here. i'd like to hear your thoughts. thanks

     i think the quote you said is actually referencing content for Vine. i did not spend any time watching any popular vine channels. but what i have done is listen to 1000s and 1000s and 1000s of songs from the past 100 years. and i've seen a lot of video content. it's good to be very experienced, but then add a twist. always good to bring experience from one area to a completely different area. good things might happen
